      <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="font-headline text-2xl font-bold text-on-surface mb-6">FAQs on Seasonal Box Management</h2>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Can I store excess boxes long-term after peak season?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Yes, in dry conditions. Palletized boxes last 12–24 months. Some warehouses keep 10–20% buffer stock year-round for demand spikes. Others sell excess boxes to other businesses.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">What if I order too many boxes for a season?</summary>
            <p class="font-body text-on-surface text-sm mt-3 leading-relaxed">Store for next year, sell to other retailers, or donate to community organizations. Build relationships with box resellers who can absorb excess inventory quickly.</p>
          </details>

          <details class="group border border-outline-variant/20 rounded-lg p-4">
            <summary class="font-label font-bold text-on-surface cursor-pointer">Can I order multiple sizes in a single seasonal batch?</summary>
